difficulty: A task was easy if it was a simple question involving just one data point and the chart was easy to read on the screen without scrolling back and front. A chart was more difficult if it contained questions involving more than one data point or when the chart was difficult to read or was formatted in a way that the data was difficult to access
format: I was satisfied with the format when it was easy to read, when most of the rows and columns fit on my screen, and when it was easy to find the data I was looking for without a lot of scrolling
